Subject: Remembering Leonard Nimoy
Description: As Mr. Spock on Star Trek, Leonard Nimoy created a character that is still influencing not only pop culture but scientific and space research. As a man, we have learned he is multi-talented and an ideal many of us hope our icons can live up to. Let us remember the man who was and was not Spock.  Speakers include:Jeanne Szarama, Mark Oshiro, Jen Talley - Track: Film  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: Microphone
